<!-- ===============================================
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
================================================ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">A family-friendly bayside suburb with strong school catchments and the bayside lifestyle access that makes the eastern corridor worth the move.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Manly West sits approximately fifteen kilometres east of the Brisbane CBD in the bayside corridor, occupying an inland position adjacent to the premium bayside suburb of Manly. The suburb is defined by family-oriented residential streets, good-sized family homes, strong school catchments, and the practical access to the Manly Boat Harbour and Cambridge Parade precinct that proximity to Manly provides. Buyers who choose Manly West have typically been comparing the eastern bayside corridor thoroughly and have concluded that the suburb delivers the school access, community character and bayside lifestyle proximity they are looking for at a price point below what a Manly address requires.
    </p>
